Package org.neo4j.procedure.impl

Class GlobalProceduresRegistry

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.kernel.lifecycle.LifecycleAdapter
      • org.neo4j.procedure.impl.GlobalProceduresRegistry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    GlobalProcedures, Lifecycle
    public class GlobalProceduresRegistry
extends LifecycleAdapter
implements GlobalProcedures
    This is the coordinating service for procedures in the DBMS. It loads procedures from a specified directory at startup, but also allows programmatic registration of them - and then, of course, allows invoking procedures.

        public <T> void registerComponent​(Class<T> cls,
                                  ThrowingFunction<Context,​T,​ProcedureException> provider,
                                  boolean safe)
        Registers a component, these become available in reflective procedures for injection.
        Specified by:
        registerComponent in interface GlobalProcedures
        Parameters:
        cls - the type of component to be registered (this is what users 'ask' for in their field declaration)
        provider - a function that supplies the component, given the context of a procedure invocation
        safe - set to false if this component can bypass security, true if it respects security
